Ever since La Palapita closed, Mini Palapita has become my go to place for steak burritos. The place is a dive, but that's its charm. A huge outdoor patio that faces Elston Ave. Haven't used it, but it's there just in case. There is interior seating is at a bare minimum. The outdoor patio has three times the capacity than the interior.  As far as the food, it is hands down the steak super burrito!! So juicy! The flavor just explodes in your mouth and dances on your taste buds!! I'm salivating just by writing about it!!! The steak is encased in a bed of lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, onion, cilantro, and guacamole. Wrapped in a flour tortilla. It's big and very filling. As of this writing a little over $11.00 tax included. Combined with a friendly and efficient staff, I'm in and out of there in less than 10 minutes and on my way home with a meal fit for a king!  Don't forget to check in with the Yelp app for your free small guacamole. Which, by the way, is also very good.

I decided to try this place for lunch.  I'm glad I stopped in. I had a couple of tacos. The first was a pork taco. It was okay. The pork had nice flavor, but was a little tough. I also had a steak taco. This taco was really good. The steak was tender, juicy and full of flavor. They also have something called Black Salsa. Yum! I really liked the flavor of the black salsa, the green was also very good. When you eat there, you can get a basket of chips. The chips were very light and flaky. The flavor was very good and went well with the two salsas. The people were very nice and the place is clean. The Elston bike lane runs right in front of the place. The only problem is they don't have a place to lock up your bicycle. There is a cement, unused driveway on the north side of the building that would be a perfect spot to install a bike rack.  I will be returning!

Tacos! Tacos! Tacos! Good portions, great flavor and taste amazing . Small place but plenty of outdoor seating. Fresh hibiscus and orchata flavor water, my two favorites and never overcrowded.  Card friendly.
Great little taqueria, no frills.  Food is reasonable and the late hours are great for weekends.
